value.value: An heterocyclic antineoplastic antibiotic isolated from the bacterium Actinomycete strain J907-21.  Elsamitrucin intercalates into DNA at guanine-cytosine (G-C)-rich sequences and inhibits topoisomerase I and II, resulting in single-strand breaks and inhibition of DNA replication. (NCI04)

The area in the United States comprised of a 68 square mile area northeast of the Potomac River donated by the state of Maryland.  The District of Columbia, also known as D.C., is not a state, nor is it part of any state.  It is a "federal district" established by the US Constitution as the seat of government. The district is occupied entirely by the city of Washington.
A regimen consisting of oral cyclophosphamide and methotrexate that may be used in the treatment of metastatic breast cancer.
